    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>Yesterday only I received <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Lowâ€™s</persName>
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0058">MS.S.</title></bibl> the book of
                    prints, &amp; the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0159">annals of
                            Scotland</title></bibl>. I shall in the course of this winter give the
                        <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0058">Tour of the
                        orknies</title></bibl> a very careful perusal; &amp; select such prints as I
                    think will best promote its sale. I give you many thanks for the prints which
                    are very acceptable. I beg to know who etched &amp; drew them, &amp; whether
                    some are not taken from old drawings being in a far more perfect state than when
                    I saw the place for example <placeName ref="pl0215">Kilchurrn castle</placeName>
                    &amp; others quite altered e.g. <placeName ref="pl0352">Melvile
                        castle</placeName>, if that which <persName ref="pe0091">Lord
                        Levin</persName> lives at.</p>
                <p>My respectful complim<hi rend="superscript">ts</hi> attend <persName ref="pe0064">Sir D<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> Dalrymple</persName> &amp; thanks for
                    his most acceptable present. I had bought a copy but will retain this as a
                    memorial of the honor he does me in thinking of me, if he has not my <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0012">Welsh Tour</title></bibl>, please to
                    present one to him in my name from <persName ref="pe0192">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Elliot</persName>.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> faithful humble
                            Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                    <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Sept<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 17<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> 1779.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom House</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
                <p><hi rend="superscript">FREE</hi><persName ref="pe0015">RMostyn</persName></p>
